      },
      "date": "2014-04-17 16:21:35.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nThe verbose mount option is infrequently used, so it doesn't go very far notifying the user that the block tunables were changed. Our preferred solution would be emitting a message to  syslog if max_sectors_kb is tuned below a threshold (1MB, 4MB, or max request size) advising that changes are made within udev.\n\n\nA log message to syslog would be preferable, because if there is a problem, it would likely get seen.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
